This paper belongs to the sub-category of AI called Genetic Algorithms. 

Explanation: 
The paper discusses the concept of "collective adaptation" which involves the sharing of building blocks among individuals in a population. This is similar to the process of crossover in genetic algorithms, where genetic material is exchanged between individuals to create new offspring with desirable traits. The paper also mentions the use of fitness functions to evaluate the performance of individuals in the population, which is a key component of genetic algorithms. Therefore, this paper is most related to the sub-category of AI called Genetic Algorithms.
